I already said 4 days ago, that you can force PyTorch to be built by suppressing all warnings with "-w" It is not a solution, it is a work-around. Modify CMake*.txt, find where all the flags are being passed to the C compiler and put a new line in front with the "-w" flag.

body:
I already said 4 days ago, that you can force PyTorch to be built by
suppressing all warnings with "-w" It is not a solution, it is a
work-around.
Modify CMake*.txt, find where all the flags are being passed to the C
compiler and put a new line in front with the "-w" flag.
